quran[42]{c,v,t,f}:
  80,1,"He [i.e., the Prophet (ﷺ) ] frowned and turned away",""
  80,2,"Because there came to him the blind man,[1] [interrupting].","[1] ʿAbdullāh, the son of Umm Maktūm."
  80,3,"But what would make you perceive, [O Muḥammad], that perhaps he might be purified[1]","[1] As a result of what he learns from you."
  80,4,"Or be reminded and the remembrance would benefit him?",""
  80,5,"As for he who thinks himself without need,[1]","[1] i.e., without need of faith or need of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) . Here it is in reference to a certain influential member of the Quraysh whom the Prophet (ﷺ) had hoped to bring to Islām."
  80,6,"To him you give attention.",""
  80,7,"And not upon you [is any blame] if he will not be purified.[1]","[1] The Prophet (ﷺ) was responsible only for conveying the message, not for ultimate guidance."
  80,8,"But as for he who came to you striving [for knowledge]",""
  80,9,"While he fears [Allāh],",""
  80,10,"From him you are distracted.",""
  80,11,"No! Indeed, they [i.e., these verses] are a reminder;",""
  80,12,"So whoever wills may remember it.[1]","[1] The revelation. Or \"Him,\" i.e., Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) ."
  80,13,"[It is recorded] in honored sheets,",""
  80,14,"Exalted and purified,",""
  80,15,"[Carried] by the hands of messenger-angels,",""
  80,16,"Noble and dutiful.",""
  80,17,"Destroyed [i.e., cursed] is man;[1] how disbelieving is he.","[1] i.e., those who deny Allāh's message."
  80,18,"From what thing [i.e., substance] did He create him?",""
  80,19,"From a sperm-drop He created him and destined for him;[1]","[1] His proportions, provisions, life span, etc."
  80,20,"Then He eased the way for him;[1]","[1] Into this world (i.e., his birth) . It may also refer to life itself, which has been made easier by Allāh's guidance."
  80,21,"Then He causes his death and provides a grave for him.[1]","[1] To conceal his decaying body."
  80,22,"Then when He wills, He will resurrect him.",""
  80,23,"No! He [i.e., man] has not yet accomplished what He commanded him.",""
  80,24,"Then let mankind look at his food -",""
  80,25,"How We poured down water in torrents,",""
  80,26,"Then We broke open the earth, splitting [it with sprouts],",""
  80,27,"And caused to grow within it grain",""
  80,28,"And grapes and herbage",""
  80,29,"And olive and palm trees",""
  80,30,"And gardens of dense shrubbery",""
  80,31,"And fruit and grass -",""
  80,32,"[As] enjoyment [i.e., provision] for you and your grazing livestock.",""
  80,33,"But when there comes the Deafening Blast[1]","[1] The piercing blast of the Horn which signals resurrection. Aṣ-Ṣākhkhah is also a name for the Day of Resurrection."
  80,34,"On the Day a man will flee from his brother",""
  80,35,"And his mother and his father",""
  80,36,"And his wife and his children,",""
  80,37,"For every man, that Day, will be a matter adequate for him.[1]","[1] i.e., to occupy him. He will be concerned only with himself, thus forgetting all others."
  80,38,"[Some] faces, that Day, will be bright -",""
  80,39,"Laughing, rejoicing at good news.",""
  80,40,"And [other] faces, that Day, will have upon them dust.",""
  80,41,"Blackness will cover them.",""
  80,42,"Those are the disbelievers, the wicked ones.",""
